Mt Banahaw is considered to be a holy mountain and is popular among pilgrims to visit this spiritually charged place, It is over 2,000 meters high, and has many sacred springs which the people believe that the water is holy and has healing powers. There are caves, streams and rocks which appear to some people to be holy illusions. Famous for hiking, there are four trails to the top which can take up to 8 hours to climb.
